 203                     current += c

 207                     raise self.parse_error()

 210                 parts += 1
 211 
 212                 current = ""
 213                 t = KeyType.Bare
 214                 continue
 215             elif c in {"'", '"'}:

 261     def _parse_item(self):  # type: () -> Optional[Tuple[Optional[Key], Item]]
 262         """
 263         Attempts to parse the next item and returns it, along with its key
 264         if the item is value-like.
 265         """
 266         self.mark()
 267         with self._state as state:
 268             while True:
 269                 c = self._current
 270                 if c == "\n":
 271                     # Found a newline; Return all whitespace found up to this point.
 272                     self.inc()
 273 
 274                     return None, Whitespace(self.extract())
 275                 elif c in " \t\r":
 276                     # Skip whitespace.
 277                     if not self.inc():
 278                         return None, Whitespace(self.extract())
 279                 elif c == "#":
 280                     # Found a comment, parse it
 281                     indent = self.extract()
 282                     cws, comment, trail = self._parse_comment_trail()
 283 
 284                     return None, Comment(Trivia(indent, cws, comment, trail))
 285                 elif c == "[":
 286                     # Found a table, delegate to the calling function.
 287                     return
 288                 else:
 289                     # Begining of a KV pair.
 290                     # Return to beginning of whitespace so it gets included
 291                     # as indentation for the KV about to be parsed.
 292                     state.restore = True
 293                     break

 295         return self._parse_key_value(True)

 721     def _parse_number(self, raw, trivia):  # type: (str, Trivia) -> Optional[Item]
 722         # Leading zeros are not allowed
 723         sign = ""
 724         if raw.startswith(("+", "-")):
 725             sign = raw[0]
 726             raw = raw[1:]
 727 
 728         if (
 729             len(raw) > 1
 730             and raw.startswith("0")
 731             and not raw.startswith(("0.", "0o", "0x", "0b"))
 732         ):
 733             return
 734 
 735         if raw.startswith(("0o", "0x", "0b")) and sign:
 736             return
 737 
 738         digits = "[0-9]"
 739         base = 10
 740         if raw.startswith("0b"):
 741             digits = "[01]"
 742             base = 2
 743         elif raw.startswith("0o"):
 744             digits = "[0-7]"
 745             base = 8
 746         elif raw.startswith("0x"):
 747             digits = "[0-9a-f]"
 748             base = 16
 749 
 750         # Underscores should be surrounded by digits
 751         clean = re.sub("(?i)(?<={})_(?={})".format(digits, digits), "", raw)
 752 
 753         if "_" in clean:
 754             return
 755 
 756         if clean.endswith("."):
 757             return
 758 
 759         try:
 760             return Integer(int(sign + clean, base), trivia, sign + raw)
 761         except ValueError:
 762             try:
 763                 return Float(float(sign + clean), trivia, sign + raw)
 764             except ValueError:
 765                 return
